news.title: Brigade Enterprises' sales bookings up 14% Rs 1,995 crore in Apr-Dec 2022
news.para: Out of the total sales bookings, the housing segment contributed Rs 1,957.4 crore, up 17 per cent from Rs 1,668.2 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Government aims to provide pakka houses: Andhra Pradesh housing minister
news.para: On the final day, Saturday, the minister visited the layouts in Chodavaram and Yelamanchili constituencies in the Visakhapatnam district.

news.title: Don't just file complaint, act against illegal buildings: Kolkata Mayor
news.para: Hakim received a call during the talk-to-mayor programme from a Beckbagan resident, who complained about an illegal construction. He also asked the concerned department to show-cause an official regarding this.

news.title: BMC is authorised to crack down on unsafe buildings: Bombay HC
news.para: “People losing lives in building collapses need to be completely obliterated. The right to livelihood, in our opinion, includes the right to live in safe building and houses,’’ said Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice Girish Kulkarni.

news.title: No water for houses illegally connected to supply network: Mysuru civic body
news.para: The Mysuru City Corporation, which is affected by mounting water bill dues, has decided to launch a drive to disconnect 40,000 water connections that are drawn illegally. The water supply lines are drawn without adopting water meters, which is affecting MCC’s revenue.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body commissioner seeks state-level probe on illegal buildings
news.para: In a letter to the principal secretary of local bodies department, Sabharwal has requested for a thorough probe into the issue while mentioning that it involved financial matter.

news.title: To cut housing delay, Haryana to give clearances before licence, says CM
news.para: Making the announcement, chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar said, “Any developer, on the basis of a letter of intent (LOI), will be granted all the necessary clearances within six months, after which they will be issued a licence for the project.”

news.title: Builders to appoint nodal officers for complaints: Haryana RERA chairman
news.para: Khandelwal further said the authority may order an audit of any building constructed within the last five years with construction quality or structural issues.

news.title: TNHB's two high-rise projects in Trichy will be completed as per schedule: Collector
news.para: The 464 dwelling units in the four high-rise towers -- each having 14-15 floors -- will be utilised under the Tamil Nadu Government Rental Housing Scheme (TNGRHS) to serve as residential quarters for the government employees.

news.title: China urges banks, insurers to support affordable rental housing
news.para: The China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission urged commercial banks to undertake affordable rental housing projects, according to a statement published on its website on Friday.

news.title: First-time home buyers in Jammu & Kashmir to get 50% stamp duty remission
news.para: The decision is aimed at giving a boost to the real-estate sector in Jammu and Kashmir and motivating the new buyers to participate in the market, he said.

news.title: Government 'soft' on illegal constructions in Ludhiana?
news.para: s the inquiry report submitted by additional commissioner Rishipal Singh has highlighted clear apathy of building branch officials, the MC Commissioner Pardeep Sabharwal has issued the show cause notices to over 100 employees, which many believe is a mere formality.

news.title: Telangana HC orders plots registrations with riders
news.para: While the case is now pending in Supreme Court after the state challenged it, the division bench order still stands as the SC did not stay it.

news.title: Nagpur civic body makes building plans, sanction charges must to construct in slums
news.para: NMC executive engineer and ‘competent authority (slum)’ Avinash Barhate issued a gazette notification on February 18 making it mandatory to get prior sanction of building plan from him for construction of houses in notified slum areas. As per state government norms, such notification needs to be issued every two years.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board e-auction finds five takers for 143 properties
news.para: An MIG (middle income group) flat in Sector 51 was sold for Rs 96.01 lakh against a reserve price of Rs 90 lakh; and another MIG flat in Sector 51 was sold for Rs 92.25 lakh against a reserve price of Rs 90 lakh.
